    "He served as a political correspondent for the <em>Morning Chronicle</em> and the <em>Daily News</em> in 1843, providing illustrations and text for the journal.": [],
    "In 1847 a chance meeting with artist and connoisseur <a href=\"/cavalcaselleg\">G.": [],
    "B. Cavalcaselle</a> led to a fast friendship based on art interests.": [],
    "When Cavalcaselle fled to London as a political exile, they lived in the same house in 1852.": [],
    "This proximity resulted in a collaborative effort of the first modern art histories in the English language.": [],
